{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sign in with a Bluesky account, send a post, and view the account’s posts."}],"metadata":{"title":"Getting Started with ATProtoKit","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"bluesky_logo.png"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"blue"},"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ATProtoKit is designed to make it easy for you to interact with the AT Protocol and other services built on of the technology, such as Bluesky."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-session","type":"heading","text":"Creating a session"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In order to log in, you need to create a session. To get started, create a new ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":" instance:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, you can create a session with the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Task {","    try await config.authenticate(with: \"lucy.bsky.social\", password: \"hunter2\")","}"]},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Do not use the password you typically use for signing into Bluesky: only use a specific App Password that’s in use for this instance of ATProtoKit only. To generate an App Password, go to the Bluesky website, then go to Settings > Privacy & Security > App Passwords and follow the instructions.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"important"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"do-catch"},{"type":"text","text":" block to create the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession"},{"type":"text","text":" object (if the session was successfully created) or handle the error (if an error occured):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","        try await config.authenticate(with: \"lucy.bsky.social\", password: \"hunter2\")","","        \/\/ Handle the success.","    } catch {","        \/\/ Handle the error.","    }","}"]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’ve enabled Two-Factor Authentication (via email), "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" waits for the code after the server returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AuthFactorTokenRequired"},{"type":"text","text":". Check your inbox for the code, then pass it to "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" from your UI or command-line input handler."}]}],"style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will contain, among other things, the access and refresh tokens. ATProtoKit abstracts this away for you so you don’t need to add it every time you use a method that requires an active session."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can then create an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit"},{"type":"text","text":" instance, where you can insert the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" object in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Task {","    let atProto = await ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","}"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-post","type":"heading","text":"Creating a post"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a post, first create an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoBluesky"},{"type":"text","text":" instance, with the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit"},{"type":"text","text":" instance as the parameter:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let atProtoBluesky = ATProtoBluesky(atProtoKitInstance: atProto)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoBluesky\/createPostRecord(text:inlineFacets:locales:replyTo:embed:labels:tags:creationDate:replyControls:embeddingRules:recordKey:shouldValidate:swapCommit:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method. While this method is extremely extensive, we’re only going to focus on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let postResult = try await atProtoBluesky.createPostRecord(text: \"Hello Bluesky!\")","print(postResult)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should see the post in your Bluesky account once you run this code. When the method successfully completes, you’ll receive a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ComAtprotoLexicon\/Repository\/StrongReference"},{"type":"text","text":" object that contains the URI of the record ("},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ComAtprotoLexicon\/Repository\/StrongReference\/recordURI"},{"type":"text","text":") and the content identifier hash of the record ("},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ComAtprotoLexicon\/Repository\/StrongReference\/recordCID"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"View-Your-Own-Posts","type":"heading","text":"View Your Own Posts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To view your own posts, you can use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit\/getAuthorFeed(by:limit:cursor:postFilter:shouldIncludePins:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession\/handle"},{"type":"text","text":" in the first argument:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["do {","    guard let session = try await atProto.getUserSession() else { return }","    let myFeed = try await atProto.getAuthorFeed(by: session.handle)","    print(\"Feed: \\(myFeed)\")","} catch {","    throw error","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, it will grab the first 50 posts from you, including replies, and without the pinned post. However, you can tweak that with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"limit"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"postFilter"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shouldIncludePins"},{"text":" arguments. You can also poll more posts if a singular call reaches its limit by using ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppBskyLexicon\/Feed\/GetAuthorFeedOutput\/cursor","isActive":true},{"text":" with the next API call:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let myFeed = try await atProto.getAuthorFeed(","    by: \"lucy.bsky.social\",","    limit: 100",")","","print(\"Feed (first 100 posts): \\(myFeed)\")","","\/\/ To get the next 100 posts, call the method again,","\/\/ but attach the `cursor` as an argument.","","let myFeedExtended = try await atProto.getAuthorFeed(","    by: \"lucy.bsky.social\",","    limit: 100,","    cursor: myFeed.cursor",")","","print(\"Feed (next 100 posts): \\(myFeedExtended)\")"]}]}],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoAdmin","doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoBluesky","doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoBlueskyChat"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/Getting-Started-with-ATProtoKit","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/getting-started-with-atprotokit"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/authenticate(with:password:)":{"title":"authenticate(with:password:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"authenticate"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"password"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentif